# UI stack (RSC + Astryx + Tailwind)

## Architecture

- Pages in `src/app/pages/` are **Server Components** by default
- Interactive Astryx forms / state live in small `"use client"` files under `src/app/components/` (see `home-form.tsx`)
- Reusable UI lives in `src/app/components/` with colocated `*.stories.tsx` (`tags: ["autodocs", "test"]`, `play` on every story — see `component-stories` rule)
- Theme: `src/app/providers.tsx` (`neutralTheme`)
- Styles: `src/app/styles.css` (Astryx + Tailwind + token bridge), linked from `Document` via `?url`
- Worker entry: `src/worker.tsx` · client: `src/client.tsx`
- Deploy: `vp run release`

## Styling (this repo overrides generic Astryx “no Tailwind” notes)

- **Astryx** for UI components (`Button`, `Card`, `VStack`, `Text`, …)
- **Tailwind** for layout wrappers and `className` overrides
- Prefer token-backed utilities: `bg-surface`, `bg-body`, `text-primary`, `text-secondary`, `rounded-lg`, …
- Escape hatch: `bg-[var(--color-background-surface)]` when a token is not bridged
- Prefer Astryx layout (`VStack`, `HStack`, `Card`) for structure; `div`/`main` wrappers with Tailwind are fine for page chrome

## Discover, don’t guess

Before inventing UI, run:

```bash
vp run astryx -- build "<idea>"
vp run astryx -- component <Name>
vp run astryx -- search "<query>"
```

Import components from `@astryxdesign/core/<Name>` (match existing pages).
